\section{\texorpdfstring{Citation\hyperref[citation]{}}{Citation}}\label{citation}

Automatic references are written as \VERB|\NormalTok{[@N4762]}| and
render as \href{https://wg21.link/n4762}{{[}N4762{]}}. Anything in
\url{https://wg21.link/index.yaml} is linked automatically.

\begin{itemize}
\tightlist
\item
  \VERB|\NormalTok{N}| Papers (e.g., \VERB|\NormalTok{[@N3887]}|
  -\textgreater{} \href{https://wg21.link/n3887}{{[}N3887{]}})
\item
  \VERB|\NormalTok{P}| Papers (e.g., \VERB|\NormalTok{[@P1371R1]}|
  -\textgreater{} \href{https://wg21.link/p1371r1}{{[}P1371R1{]}})
\item
  CWG Issues (e.g., \VERB|\NormalTok{[@CWG1234]}| -\textgreater{}
  \href{https://wg21.link/cwg1234}{{[}CWG1234{]}})
\item
  LWG Issues (e.g., \VERB|\NormalTok{[@LWG1234]}| -\textgreater{}
  \href{https://wg21.link/lwg1234}{{[}LWG1234{]}})
\item
  Github Edits (e.g., \VERB|\NormalTok{[@EDIT1234]}| -\textgreater{}
  \href{https://wg21.link/edit1234}{{[}EDIT1234{]}})
\item
  Standing Documents (e.g., \VERB|\NormalTok{[@SD6]}| -\textgreater{}
  \href{https://wg21.link/sd6}{{[}SD6{]}})
\end{itemize}

You may also write \VERB|\NormalTok{[@P2996R8]\{.title\}}| to include
the title of the paper, which renders as:
{\href{https://wg21.link/p2996r8}{{[}P2996R8{]} (Reflection for
C++26)}}.

